gly validated experimentally.', 'The hydrothermal-to-surface narrative is topologically coherent, but the chemistry is weakly aligned with the arginine literature. The upstream generation of formaldehyde, glycolaldehyde, HCN, and especially cyanamide is not supported by the supplied target-specific bundle, and several steps are chemically underjustified or overly compressed. The endpoint remains the same plausible ornithine-cyanamide route, but the precursor supply chain is speculative.', 'This pathway follows the canonical biochemical logic of arginine biosynthesis through citrulline and argininosuccinate, matching the literature as a pathway analogy. However, the supplied research explicitly states these are biochemical analog scaffolds with no established prebiotic temperatures, pH, catalysts, or yields. As a mechanistic scaffold it is coherent, but as a prebiotic synthesis route it is poorly supported.', 'This pathway compounds two major weaknesses: an unsupported HCN-to-cyanamide-to-carbamoyl-phosphate sequence and a downstream biochemical-only analog route. The literature bundle supports carbamoyl phosphate chemistry only as modern metabolic context, not prebiotic synthesis. This pathway is therefore connected as a graph narrative but poorly grounded chemically and literarily.', 'This is a long integrated route, but most of its mass lies in speculative precursor chemistry and biochemical analog transitions not validated as prebiotic. It achieves topological continuity, yet the actual literature on arginine does not support such a constructive route from hydrothermal formaldehyde through sugars and cyanamide into the biosynthetic analog sequence.', 'This pathway integrates the well-supported hydrothermal destruction step with the weakly supported biochemical analog reconstruction route. It is conceptually coherent but overstates the prebiotic credibility of the citrulline/argininosuccinate sequence. The pathway is useful as a systems narrative but not as a strong synthetic proposal.', 'The sugar-mediated convergence story adds network density, but it is weakly justified for arginine-specific chemistry. The arginine literature supplied does not support these sugar and cyanide feeder steps as demonstrated precursors to arginine. The pathway relies on a plausible terminal guanidinylation step but a largely speculative precursor scaffold.', 'This dual-convergence pathway is topologically richer than most, but its convergence is driven by poorly supported intermediates, especially carbamoyl phosphate. It mixes the only plausible direct route with biochemical analog branches that are not prebiotically established. The result is a connected but chemically uneven pathway.', 'The full integrated pathway best demonstrates cross-environment connectivity, especially the hydrothermal-to-surface and hydrothermal-sink concepts. However, much of the upstream chemistry is not supported by the arginine-specific literature, and the target literature actually emphasizes hydrothermal destruction and repeated non-detection in multiple environments. As an integrated network story it is acceptable; as a literature-grounded synthesis route it is weak.']\n\n============================================================\nAddress the above issues in your new network. Do NOT repeat the same mistakes.\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"target_molecule\": \"Arginine\",\n  \"overall_strategy\": \"This network is literature-constrained and therefore centers the only retained positive arginine-forming edge in the supplied evidence base: guanidinylation of ornithine by cyanamide in mild surface aqueous/concentrating settings. It also encodes the strongest arginine-specific counter-edge, hydrothermal destruction of arginine to ornithine, and preserves the ornithine-citrulline-argininosuccinate biochemical analog sequence strictly as mechanistic scaffold rather than demonstrated prebiotic synthesis. In direct accordance with the research bundle, explicit negative bra