nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Arginine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network is literature-constrained and therefore centers the only retained positive arginine-forming edge in the supplied evidence base: guanidinylation of ornithine by cyanamide in mild surface aqueous/concentrating settings. It also encodes the strongest arginine-specific counter-edge, hydrothermal destruction of arginine to ornithine, and preserves the ornithine-citrulline-argininosuccinate biochemical analog sequence strictly as mechanistic scaffold rather than demonstrated prebiotic synthesis. In direct accordance with the research bundle, explicit negative branches are included for spark-discharge, sulfur-rich spark-discharge, ice photolysis, meteoritic inventory, and mixed-valence iron hydrothermal mineral systems, each terminating in non-arginine outcomes. Because the literature does not provide a validated abiotic ornithine synthesis route with exact conditions, ornithine is treated as an available precursor/hub rather than invented de novo. The 10 pathways therefore represent distinct literature-grounded traversals and environmental narratives converging on arginine or on arginine-relevant sink/scaffold states, while keeping all nodes connected in one bipartite graph.\n\nMOLECULES (20 nodes):\n  - mol_001: C5H12N2O2 (ornithine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_002: CH2N2 (cyanamide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_003: C6H14N4O2 (arginine) [target]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: CH4N2O3P-2 (carbamoyl phosphate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C6H13N3O3 (citrulline) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C4H7NO4 (aspartate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C10H18N4O6 (argininosuccinate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C4H4O4 (fumarate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: CH4 (methane) [starting]\n  - mol_011: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_012: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - m