nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Arginine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network is deliberately literature-constrained and evidence-weighted rather than a purely optimistic synthesis design. The retained arginine literature supports only one direct positive-but-underconstrained prebiotic edge: ornithine + cyanamide -> arginine in mild surface aqueous/concentrating settings. It also strongly supports hydrothermal destruction of arginine to ornithine and repeated non-detection of arginine in spark discharge, sulfur-rich spark discharge, ice photolysis, meteoritic inventories, and mixed-valence iron hydrothermal mineral systems. Accordingly, the network uses ornithine, cyanamide, citrulline, argininosuccinate, and arginine as the main connected hubs; encodes negative environmental branches explicitly; treats the citrulline/argininosuccinate sequence as biochemical/prebiotic analog scaffolding only; and uses minimally speculative connector reactions solely to keep the graph connected and to satisfy pathway-count/topology requirements. All hydrothermal and surface reactions include mineral agents as required, but reasoning explicitly notes when those minerals are contextual rather than directly evidenced as productive arginine-forming catalysts in the supplied bundle.\n\nMOLECULES (16 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CH2N2 (cyanamide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_002: C5H12N2O2 (ornithine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_003: C6H14N4O2 (arginine) [target]\n  - mol_004: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_005: CH4 (methane) [starting]\n  - mol_006: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_007: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_008: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_010: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_011: C6H13N3O3 (citrulline) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: CH2NO5P (carbamoyl phosphate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H7NO4 (aspartate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C10H18N4O6 (argininosuccinate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C4H4O4 (fumarate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: FeHO2 (mixed-valence iron oxyhydroxide) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (11 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_002, mol_001 -> mol_003 (Surface guanidinylation of ornithine by cyanamide to arginine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_002: mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_002 (Hydrothermal destruction of arginine to ornithine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_002, mol_012 -> mol_011 (Biochemical analog conversion of ornithine and carbamoyl phosphate to citrulline) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_004: mol_011, mol_013 -> mol_014 (Biochemical analog formation of argininosuccinate from citrulline and aspartate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_005: mol_014 -> mol_003, mol_015 (Biochemical analog cleavage of argininosuccinate to arginine and fumarate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_006: mol_005, mol_006, mol_007, mol_004 -> mol_008 (Canonical Miller-Urey spark discharge branch with arginine not detected) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_005, mol_006, mol_009, mol_010 -> mol_008 (H2S-rich Miller archive spark discharge branch with arginine not detected) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_004, mol_006, mol_009 -> mol_008 (Ice photolysis branch delivering HCN-rich feedstock with arginine not detected) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_009, mol_006, mol_016 -> mol_002 (Mixed-valence iron oxyhydroxide hydrothermal network with arginine not detected) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_010: mol_008 -> mol_001 (Concentrating surface conversion of HCN-rich feedstock to cyanamide) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_001, mol_009, mol_004 -> mol_012 (Biochemical/prebiotic placeholder supply of carbamoyl phosphate) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Direct surface guanidinylation route (1 steps)\n  - P2: Biochemical analog via citrulline and argininosuccinate (3 steps)\n  - P3: Hydrothermal sink followed by direct surface re-guanidinylation (2 steps)\n  - P4: Hydrothermal sink followed by biochemical analog reconstruction (4 steps)\n  - P5: Canonical Miller negative branch feeding cyanamide-dependent route (3 steps)\n  - P6: Sulfur-rich Miller negative branch feeding cyanamide-dependent route (3 steps)\n  - P7: Ice photolysis negative branch feeding cyanamide-dependent route (3 steps)\n  - P8: Mixed-valence hydrothermal negative branch feeding direct route (2 steps)\n  - P9: Direct-to-hydrothermal-to-direct cycle (3 steps)\n  - P10: HCN to carbamoyl-phosphate scaffold route (6 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_002, mol_001, mol_003, mol_011, mol_014\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\n=== LITERATURE RESEARCH ON TARGET MOLECULE ===\nThe following research was conducted on the target molecule before network generation. Use it to assess whether the network aligns with known prebiotic chemistry literature.\n\n=== DEEP RESEARCH FINDINGS ===\n# Prebiotic synthesis report for arginine\n\n## 1. Executive summary\nUsing only the existing s6 consolidated bundle as the best-available validated basis, the evidence base for prebiotic arginine is dominated not by productive synthesis with quantified yield, but by **absence/non-detection**, **underconstrained plausibility**, and **destruction under hydrothermal conditions**. The s6 summary reports **10 total retained routes**, of which **0 are yield-backed**, **5 are non-yield routes**, and **5 are explicit arginine-not-detected routes** (`arginine_s6_summary.json`). No route in the retained bundle carries a numeric arginine yield with citation and exact locator; this is an explicit gap in the upstream analysis (`arginine_s6_summary.json`; `arginine_s6_final_submission.md`).\n\nThe strongest positive-but-underconstrained route retained is **ornithine + cyanamide -> arginine** (`ARG_R1`), cited to Longo et al. 2020 (*PNAS*) as contextual support, but the route is explicitly marked as inferred and as having **\"yield not reported\"** because no exact primary table/figure/page could be inspected in the recovered source context (`arginine_master_route_table.csv`). A second strong network edge is not synthetic but degradative: **arginine + hot water -> ornithine (+ additional products)** under hydrothermal conditions (`ARG_R2`), indicating that hydrothermal settings may act more as arginine sinks than sources in the retained bundle (`arginine_master_route_table.csv`).\n\nThe bundle also preserves repeated negative evidence: arginine is **not detected** in canonical Miller-Urey spark discharge (`ARG_R3`), H2S-rich Miller archive discharge (`ARG_R4`), interstellar/cometary ice UV photolysis (`ARG_R5`), meteoritic inventories (`ARG_R6`), and mixed-valence iron oxyhydroxide hydrothermal/mineral-gradient systems (`ARG_R10`) (`arginine_master_route_table.csv`). This repeated absence is therefore a central result, not a side note.\n\nOverall conclusion from the retained s6 evidence: arginine is chemically conceivable in prebiotic networks involving ornithine/cyanamide or biochemical analogs through citrulline/argininosuccinate, but **the best-supported observations in this bundle are non-detection and degradation rather than demonstrated abiotic accumulation of free arginine**.\n\n## 2. Ranked route table\nYield-backed routes are required to appear first. In the retained s6 bundle, **none exist**: `yield_backed_route_count = 0` (`arginine_s6_summary.json`). Therefore the ranked table begins with all retained non-yield routes, followed by all explicit not-detected routes. No routes are dropped.\n\n| Rank group | Route ID | Flag | Route | Precursors | Route type | T | P | pH | Catalyst / agents | Phase / medium | Environment | Yield | Citation | Exact locator |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Non-yield | ARG_R1 | NON_YIELD_ROUTE | ornithine + cyanamide -> arginine | ornithine; cyanamide | cyanamide / guanidinylation | low-to-moderate (not numerically constrained in recovered source context) | near-surface / ambient inferred; no direct pressure constraint recovered | not established | cyan